      <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          <strong>🇰🇷 South Korean President arrested</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">After constant standoffs with authorities and investigators, impeached South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol was arrested. This makes him the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-01-2025-br1-8-first-sitting-president" target="_blank">first sitting president</a> in South Korea to be arrested. His arrest team, made up of over 1000 people, had to scale his barricades and cut through barbed wire to get to him while simultaneously battling it out with Yoon’s security team. He remains uncooperative and believes the warrant is not legally valid. Yoon is currently suspended and impeached by parliament. A ruling has yet to be made by South Korea’s Constitutional Court on his official removal. South Korean Foreign Minister Cho Tae-yul met with Japanese Foreign Minister Takeshi Iwaya to discuss regional security amid the political crisis.</p>
        </mj-text>
